Note:
Recursively fold a body array in place.

  parent          - pointer to the parent struct (function, STMT_IF, STMT_WHILE,
                    STMT_FOR_RANGE, STMT_FOR_EACH, match-arm) whose body field
                    we are folding.
  body_ptr_offset - byte offset within parent of the body-pointer field
                    (`Statement**`, 8 bytes).
  count_offset    - byte offset within parent of the count field (int32).

The function reads the body+count, walks each statement, and for each
STMT_IF whose condition folds, splices the taken branch into the parent
body array (reallocating it). After splice, the iterator index is reset to
the splice point so the spliced-in statements are themselves walked and
any nested folds happen.

For all compound statements that survive (or were not foldable), recurses
into their child body arrays in the same way.
