                        Note: (defensive - parser should not emit them).
                        If branch_count is less than 0:
                            Set branch_count to 0
                        End If
                        Note: Replace body[i] (the STMT_IF) with
                        Note: branch_body[0..branch_count-1]. New body
                        Note: length = body_count - 1 + branch_count.
                        Let new_count be body_count minus 1
                        Set new_count to new_count plus branch_count
                        If new_count is equal to 0:
                            Note: Spliced everything out. Set the body to
                            Note: 0 / count 0. Old body memory is leaked
                            Note: (parse-time arena; freed at process end).
                            memory_set_pointer(parent, body_ptr_offset, 0)
                            memory_set_int32(parent, count_offset, 0)
                            Set body to 0
                            Set body_count to 0
                            Set i to 0
                        Otherwise:
